text.tspan: Figure i. The convergence process for decoding "needed" with N=1000. Each plot is
showing the coefficients for the guess of each letter. The earliest iterations are in black
and the later iterations are in copper. As the correct answer is inferred, these distributions
become more and more peaked. Each iteration uses these distributions as the guess for
the next iteration. The more peaked the distribution, the less noisy the decoding will be.
